        <briefdescription>
<para>Fill <computeroutput>w</computeroutput> with a Kaiser window of shape parameter <computeroutput>beta</computeroutput>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Uses the Bessel function I0 via a converging power series.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>w</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Output buffer, length <computeroutput>w_len</computeroutput> (modified in-place). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>w_len</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Window length &gt;= 1. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>beta</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Shape parameter (higher = more attenuation, wider main lobe). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
